> classes are defined as final entities at compile time, then used at run time.<p>This isn't exactly true.  PHP objects can have dynamically assigned members without having magic methods defined.  e.g.<p><pre><code>    $foo = new stdClass();
    $foo->bar = "baz";
    echo $foo->bar; //"baz"
</code></pre>
And now, with "closures", those members can be methods.
